### **4.2 Veto-Mechanismus (Smart Contract)**
#### **📌 Logik**
- Falls **Temperatur > 40°C** oder **pH < 6,5** → **Freigabe wird blockiert**.
- **Smart Contract-Code:**
```solidity
function checkVetoConditions(uint256 temperature, uint256 ph) public view returns (bool) {
    if (temperature > 40 || ph < 6.5) {
        return true; // Veto aktiviert
    }
    return false;
}

function releaseBatch(bytes32 _hash) external nonReentrant {
    require(!checkVetoConditions(sensorData.temperature, sensorData.ph), "Veto condition met");
    require(batches[_hash].cqaScore > 95, "Batch not notarized");
    emit BatchReleased(_hash);
}
```

